OL,3,C'They've taken my life too' - murdered
OL,4,Cboy's mum sees teen killers sentenced
OL,6,F"I still didn't believe it. I still
OL,7,Fdon't. His bedroom's the same, I
OL,8,Fhaven't changed anything. It's the
OL,9,Fsame as that morning when he went out.
OL,11,F"His shoes are still by the front door
OL,12,Fand the back door. His coat is still
OL,13,Fon the coat stand.
OL,15,F"The only way I can get through it is
OL,16,Fto think: 'He'll be home soon'.
OL,18,F"The worst bit is coming home. It's
OL,19,Fhard because he's not here when I get
OL,20,Fback and I used to look forward to
OL,21,Fcoming home to him", she added.
